<li><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/library/world/africa/index-congo-1998.html" class="external text" title="http://www.nytimes.com/library/world/africa/index-congo-1998.html" rel="nofollow">New York Times section on Civil War in Congo</a> with extensive background</li>
<li><a href="http://www.un.org/Depts/dpko/missions/monuc/index.html" class="external text" title="http://www.un.org/Depts/dpko/missions/monuc/index.html" rel="nofollow">UN Mission in Congo</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/world/africa/centralafrica/democraticrepubliccongo/" class="external text" title="http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/world/africa/centralafrica/democraticrepubliccongo/" rel="nofollow">Washington Post site</a> with updated news stories on the DRC</li>
<li><a href="http://www.ushmm.org/museum/exhibit/online/congojournal" class="external text" title="http://www.ushmm.org/museum/exhibit/online/congojournal" rel="nofollow">United States Holocaust Memorial Museum - Ripples of Genocide: Journey Through Eastern Congo</a> The journal depicted in this Web site is compiled from the impressions and contributions of UNHCR Goodwill Ambassador Angelina Jolie, John Prendergast of the International Crisis Group, and two photographers.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kpd3ykS4QOQ&amp;feature=PlayList&amp;p=8393C24D166F28BD&amp;index=11" class="external text" title="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kpd3ykS4QOQ&amp;feature=PlayList&amp;p=8393C24D166F28BD&amp;index=11" rel="nofollow">Children of Conflic</a>, a video documentary on <a href="/wiki/Youtube" title="Youtube" class="mw-redirect">Youtube</a> broadcast by <a href="/wiki/AlJazeera" title="AlJazeera" class="mw-redirect">AlJazeera</a> TV.</li>
